title: Latvia Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Latvia Three Month Interbank Rate was at 0.17 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Latvia averaged 3.03 percent from 1997 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 23.50 percent in June of 2009 and a record low of 0.16 percent in October of 2013. In Latvia, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Latvia Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank of Latvia
